// Setup Steps:
git init
touch server.js .gitignore   
npm intit -y
node_modules >> .gitignore

// Packages to install
 npm i express   

// Seuelize stup steps
 npm i sequelize pg rowdy-logger  
   sequelize init  
Update config.jspon 
    change dialect to postgres
    update database name

// General
express application handles the server

npm start to run files (package.jspon)

by default, browser runs get request to the root directory

ctrl c to kill terminal
-run npm start again

run nodemon to have the server automatically update

making a restful api for our web app

CRUD    - Action            - HTTP verbs  - Endpoint
========================================================
CREATE  - Create            - POST        - /resource
READ    - Show (Read one)   - GET         - /resource
READ    - Index (Read all)  - GET         - /resource/id
UPDATE  - Update            - PUT         - /resource/id
DELETE  - Delete            - DELETE      - /resource/id

rowdy -logger